<br>
I consider myself as an always-scared-Mage, but still I decided to give it a try since I did hit lvl 29 in Marus seru and was bored of the crappy-loot-MOBs...<br>
The day didn't start really good.<br>
First I wanted to look for the hidden entrance.<br>
So I arrived at the spires in shadowhaven, but because of lag or stupidity or a nervous hand I did fall into the water. No biggy I thought...and tried to get out. didnT make it. I tried it at any spot, but I didnt get out. I know how to leave water usually, but still I didn't get out ;-)<br>
So I ended up with asking some anonymous people there for a Levitate and finally somebody had the spell and helped me out. <br>
I didn't feel good ,-)<br>
<br>
Then I was at the soulbinder and looked for the false wall.<br>
Needless to say that I didn't find it ;-)<br>
<br>
But the guy who already helped me out was still standing there so I decided that I could as well ask him for more help ;-) and he showed me the hidden wall :-)<br>
<br>
So I then was in Echo Caverns.<br>
A first /who made me believe I am at the wrong place. I saw about 10 people all of whom were between 50 and 60. (now I know that they were probably just passing through ;-) )<br>
<br>
So I then followed the described way.<br>
Sometime I saw the 3 Boglings at the left side and remembered that I read &quot;ignore them or kill them as you will&quot;. So I guessed they would be an easy start, like a &quot;warm-up&quot; for my echo caverns adventure.<br>
So I casted a Fire Pet, gave it 2 Swords, medded up, casted BO2 and sent it against the middle Bogling.<br>
Then I sent a Nuke against that Bogling and targetted my Pet again...and was shocked to see it at 20 health. Tried to heal it, but failed ;-)<br>
1 second after the 3 Boglings started to hamper me like crazy.<br>
So I started to run at 60 health...<br>
Opened the steel door...40 health....allowed myself a short looking-back...1 was taken away by the guards, 2 were still chasing me.....30 health....made it to the guards at the exit...allowed myself another look...1 was still on me...20 health....zone! pooh! (When looking back I almost consider it a miracle that I found the right way, Usually I need a long time at new areas until I remember the ways well enough ;-) ).<br>
<br>
Now even more scared than before I entered again after a while. ;-)<br>
Made myself invis this time and passed the Boglings this time without even looking at them ;-) But somehow I thought &quot;If the nice and supposed easy Boglings almost killed me...what shall then happen at the &quot;main-pray&quot;? &quot; ;-) <br>
<br>
Ok found the tentactle-thingies, got around them and finally saw my first Needlite. (It was at the &quot;T&quot;)<br>
So I got my Fire Pet, gave it 2 sword...and blah blah blah....<br>
Sent it against the Needlite, nuked for 200dmg and it was already dead and I had 1 blue bubble more xp.! WOOOHOOOO!<br>
But no loot...:-(<br>
<br>
So I then allowed myself a look into the right room and was a little shocked when I saw all the Needlites ... &quot;Ummm 1 was easy...but they are so close together....how shall i stand a Chance here????&quot;<br>
But since I thought that I lived once when I was supposed to die (the Bogling thing ;-) ) I thought that I can test my luck a bit more.<br>
<br>
stepped in...sent my Pet against the first...no add...woohooo...dead...no loot...<br>
Ok the end is easy...killed the whole room without any trouble.<br>
But: no loot at all for the first round.<br>
So I was already thinking &quot;ummm...if I doint getany loot here I might have to leave..I NEED the coins!&quot;)<br>
<br>
But soon I experienced that I even have to leave some loot behind....:-(<br>
<br>
Anyway: I got more and more excited. The xp came in like crazy, the loot is nice (also got the Queen twice meanwhile: didnt get a cloak yet, but twice the dagger: sold one for 15pp and gave the other to a newbie-friend)<br>
<br>
So thanks a lot for this advice. This place REALLY rocks.<br>
(Got 4 yellow bubbles yesterday in 90 minutes playing )<br>
<br>
Just one piece of advice I can maybe give you now:<br>
(I belong to the people who cannot sell in Echo Caverns)<br>
Since it really bugged me that I have to leave the loot behind I &quot;discovered&quot; a way how I can safe most of it:<br>
I usually get Needlite Wings and Needlite Legs both of which are LORE.<br>
So if I found more than 1 of each I put &quot;excess stuff&quot; (so the items I cannot take with me) into dimensional pockets and &quot;deposit&quot; it at the &quot;T-room&quot;.<br>
Then I gate to Shadowhaven, sell, run back, pick up the other stuff and sell again.(I just REALLY need the money ;-) )<br>
<br>
Currently I dont want to kill the Boglings anyway, so I have enough time to do the selling, med up, get a new Pet+Weapon and be ready for the next spawn.<br>
<br>
I'm close to 30 now but already am looking at my lvl 34 spells which I will buy SOON ;-)<br>
<br>
